		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Per a request in a private message, I have changed the Administrators group's custom username color from #AA0000 (<strong><span style="color: #AA0000">Like This</span></strong>) to a brighter red #FF3300 (<strong><span style="color: #FF3300">Like This</span></strong>), which should have better contrast with the post background.<br /><br />What other color changes need to happen to make forums more usable?</div><br />This is a good change. In general, for color-blindedness or not, having important details differentiable by luminosity helps readability for everybody. I don't have any color-blindness, but the dark admin text was a little hard to read anyway.

		

